instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin orchestrates data, models, and algorithms within a layered architecture. Data are ingested continuously from the Physical Twin via its sensors and stored in a time‑series repository. A calibration layer of algorithms iteratively updates the cyber and physical models, producing a calibrated model set that represents the CPS and its environment. Monitoring services consume the calibrated data to enforce safety and performance constraints. Violations trigger either automated corrective action or human intervention. The system manages resources by coordinating model updates, simulation cycles, and monitor executions, ensuring that data, computational models, and control logic are coherently integrated and deployed across the Digital Twin."
]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "Development Phase: creation of abstract models (e.g., CAD representations of a car’s geometry and dynamic differential‑equation models of its motion). Representation Transition: conversion of these design‑time models into runtime models that incorporate streamed sensor data; calibration algorithms iteratively adjust model parameters to align simulated dynamics with measured physical behavior. Deployment Phase: launch of the Digital Twin framework alongside the Physical Twin, enabling real‑time monitoring and simulation. Transition Management: continuous calibration loops and parameter estimation embedded in the Digital Twin’s core engine. Governance: safety and performance monitors evaluate operational metrics; upon detection of violations, alerts trigger human review or automated corrective actions, thereby enforcing lifecycle control."
]
